  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Geographically and physically able to attend scheduled evaluations and follow-up
             appointments

          -  Indicated for cochlear implantation

          -  Age 18 years or older

          -  Fluent in German or French

          -  Sufficient facial recess size ( at least 2.6 mm or at least 0.4 mm safety margin to
             the facial nerve and chorda tympani)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Pregnancy

          -  Anatomical malformation of the middle or inner ear or unusual facial nerve course

          -  Restricted neck movement (unable to comfortably rotate neck 30 degrees)

          -  Lack of compliance with any inclusion criteria
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
